Heads of state, former heads of state and heads of international and regional organisation have started arriving for President-elect, Cyril Ramaphosa’s inauguration at Loftus Versfeld Stadium in Pretoria. Among those attending is Zimbabwean President Emmerson Mnangagwa, DRC President Felix Tshisekedi, Rwandan President Paul Kagame and Ugandan president Yoweri Museveni. His Majesty King Letsie III of the Kingdom of Lesotho and Her Majesty Queen Masenato Seeiso, and His Majesty King Mswati III of the Kingdom of eSwatini  and the African Union Chairperson, Moussa Fakiwill are also attending. Here is the full list of heads of state, former heads of state and regional organisation:   